Introduction:

The Economist is a leading source of analysis on international business and world affairs. We deliver our information through a range of formats, from newspapers and magazines to conferences and electronic services. What ties us together is the objectivity of our opinion, the originality of our insight and our advocacy of economic and political freedom around the world.

The Economist Group has a global implementation of Salesforce.com, Sales Cloud. This is spread over several businesses and different revenue streams. There is integration with related marketing products such as Marketo & Eloqua, and some use is made of the Force.com platform. In addition, The Economist Group is currently implementing a B2C Salesforce instance, which will span Communities, Service & Marketing Clouds and includes installed packages, such as Limio and Zuora; this is an exciting opportunity to be part of a Digital Transformation programme to improve our Customer Experience.

The Salesforce Developer will support the expansion of our Salesforce capabilities while working on projects from requirement gathering to design and implementation. Responsibilities will also include Salesforce configuration along with the system maintenance and customization to support business requirements, recommending opportunities for on-going improvements as appropriate. The role demands considerable Salesforce.com experience developing programmatically and to provide architectural recommendations.

This is an exciting role which will allow the successful candidate to gain exposure to multiple Salesforce Clouds and be a part of a dynamic team and interact with stakeholders across different departments and levels.
Accountabilities:
How you will contribute:
Proactively interact with stakeholders to understand Salesforce requirements and subsequently translate them into technical specifications;
Chair information gathering workshops, conduct one to one interviews and produce documents to allow data capture;
Manage delivery of functional and technical solutions and system integrations including testing strategy and execution;
Ensure proposed technical solutions meet Salesforce coding best practice and code coverage to be at 90%+;
Manage existing and build new integrations between Salesforce and other applications;
Perform and execute all functional testing;
Work with business colleagues to gain user acceptance and take up;
Create custom build reports for trend analysis using standard reports functionality as well as reporting snapshot and historical trending;
Mentor and Coach Salesforce Administrators within the team;
Create and keep Salesforce related technical documents and training materials up-to-date;
Keep up-to-date with new Salesforce releases and promptly identify features which could add value to the Economist’s Salesforce users and those which will impact existing processes and require urgent attention as required;
Ensure the Salesforce data storage is within limit - implement continuous review and corrective action;
Provide support for the day to day management of Salesforce.com; and
Perform administrative tasks such as setting up users, manage the security settings, create or update fields, page layouts, process builder and workflows, reports and dashboards and manage data using data loader or other tools.

Experience, skills and professional attributes:
The ideal skills for this role are:

Relevant bachelor’s degree (or equivalent);
At least Administrator, Platform Developer - I and Sales Cloud Certified.
In depth and progressive Salesforce experience (from administrator to developer) gained in a similar role;
Experience working on Salesforce products - Sales Cloud, Force.com, Non-profit Cloud and Community Cloud;
Develop with semi-structured data like JSON;
Knowledge of REST and SOAP API's;
Ability to design complex SOQL and SOSL queries;
The development of custom front-end Lightning components through Aura and/or Web Components
Point-and-click development within a Lightning environment;
Analysis and design through to successful implementation of Salesforce.com, including experience with Salesforce.com developer toolkit including Apex Classes, Controllers, and Triggers, Visualforce, Force.com IDE, Migration Tool, Web Services;
Ability to manage code coverage within the governance limit;
Delivering Salesforce.com training to users at all levels in terms of organisational structure and experience using Salesforce;
Experience of business analysis.
Code deployment experience using Salesforce DX with Github;
Ability to provide application users with technical and functional support.
A good understanding of data structures, data modelling, DB schema;
Exposure to Agile development methodologies and JIRA as a project management application;
A proven track record of successful project delivery with at least three full project life cycles completed;
Knowledge of Java and Javascript;
Excellent teamwork with both clients and colleagues;
